<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="38" pageId="2" pageNumber="37" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="37">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">
<pageBreakToken pageId="3" pageNumber="38" start="start">Liana</pageBreakToken>
</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Stems</emphasis>
terete, striate, interpetiolar region with ridges and glandular fields, eglandular and glandular trichomes covering the stem surface, eglandular trichomes simple, densely distributed in a hispid indument, glandular trichomes peltate and pateliform, flaky bark absent; prophylls 1.6-3 mm long, subulate, apiculate, smooth, hispid. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Leaves</emphasis>
bifoliolate with a terminal tendril; petioles semi-terete, hispid and with peltate trichomes, 0.95-4.49 cm long; petiolules terete, hispid with simple and peltate trichomes, 0.3-2.9 cm long, with equal length; tendrils trifid and uncinate; leaflets ovate, obovate or elliptic, apex acute to short acuminate with a drip tip, base rounded, symmetric or slight asymmetric, 3.2-8.6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.2-7.14 cm, margin entire, membranaceous, the abaxial surface hispid with simple trichomes more concentrated on the veins, peltate trichomes throughout and pateliform glandular trichomes concentrated at the base, the adaxial surface hispid, primary venation straight, unbranched, secondary venation brochidodromous and tertiary venation percurrent. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Inflorescence</emphasis>
an axillary 3-flowered cyme, rarely reduced to one flower; pedicels 0.5-4.3 cm long, hispid and with peltate glandular trichomes; receptacle with pateliform trichomes; bracts deciduous, floral bracts filiform, deciduous, rarely present, elliptic to obovate, 0.7-5.5 mm long, membranaceous. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Calyx</emphasis>
green, bi-lobed, spathaceous with an incurved apicule, 1.4-3.2 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.7-1.6 cm, membranaceous, glabrate to hispidulous, with peltate trichomes. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Corolla</emphasis>
yellow, bilabiate with the upper 2 lobes reflexed and the lower 3 lobes forward, tubular-infundibuliform, glabrate, hispidulous 5.1-9.1 cm long, 1.3-2.2 cm, 4-5.7 cm wide; lobes obcordate, 1.2-2 cm long, 1.2-2.15 cm wide, margin entire. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Androecium</emphasis>
inserted at the tube, with simple trichomes at the insertion; short filaments 1.15-1.7 cm long, longer filaments 1.74-2.4 cm long, glabrous, attached at the same height from the base of the corolla, 4.5-9.4 mm from the base; staminode 8-9 mm long; anthers pale-yellow or white, 3-3.9 mm long. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Gynoecium</emphasis>
inserted at the tube, glabrous; pistil 3.3-3.8 cm long; ovary vinaceus, linear, 7-9 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.4 mm long; style 2.6-3 cm long; stigma rhombic. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Fruits</emphasis>
linear, attenuate toward base and apex, 77-125.8 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.17-2.2 cm, smooth, with lenticels, glabrous. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Seeds</emphasis>
with hyaline wings, thin, 2.2-3.8 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.4-1.8 cm wide, seed body oblong to ovoid, woody, 6-9 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
8-15 mm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="38" type="nomenclatural notes">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Nomenclatural notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="38">
A single specimen was cited by Sonder for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fonseca &amp; Cabral &amp; Agra &amp; Lohmann" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="Fonseca &amp; Cabral &amp; Agra &amp; Lohmann" baseAuthorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Bignoniaceae" genus="Spathodea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Spathodea mollis" order="Lamiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mollis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Spathodea mollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
labeled 292 in 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Regnell’s">Regnell's</normalizedToken>
first series of collections from Brazil. Four specimens labeled as Regnell I-292 were located, one at K [000449792], two at BR [876279] [876378] and one at MO [2229711]. The best quality material is selected here as lectotype.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="39" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" type="taxonomic notes">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Taxonomic notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="39">
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. H. Fonseca &amp; L. G. Lohmann" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="Fonseca &amp; Cabral &amp; Agra &amp; Lohmann" baseAuthorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Bignoniaceae" genus="Dolichandra" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Dolichandra hispida" order="Lamiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hispida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">
<pageBreakToken pageId="4" pageNumber="39" start="start">Dolichandra</pageBreakToken>
hispida
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily differentiated from all other species of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Bignoniaceae" genus="Dolichandra" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Dolichandra" order="Lamiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">Dolichandra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the unique hispid indument found on the vegetative and reproductive portions of this species, as well as the presence of a vinaceus ovary. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. H. Fonseca &amp; L. G. Lohmann" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="Fonseca &amp; Cabral &amp; Agra &amp; Lohmann" baseAuthorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Bignoniaceae" genus="Dolichandra" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Dolichandra hispida" order="Lamiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hispida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">Dolichandra hispida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been treated as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Bignoniaceae" genus="Dolichandra" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Dolichandra uncata" order="Lamiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="uncata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">Dolichandra uncata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
since 
<bibRefCitation author="Gentry, AH" journalOrPublisher="Annals of Missouri Botanical Garden" pageId="6" pageNumber="41" pagination="781 - 977" publicationUrl="10.2307/2395140" refId="B3" refString="Gentry, AH, 1973a. Flora of Panama: Bignoniaceae. Annals of Missouri Botanical Garden 60: 781 - 977, DOI: 10.2307/2395140" title="Flora of Panama: Bignoniaceae." url="10.2307/2395140" volume="60" year="1973 a">Gentry (1973a)</bibRefCitation>
. However, the differences in indument (hispid vs. glabrous to puberulous), ovary color (vinaceus in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. H. Fonseca &amp; L. G. Lohmann" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="Fonseca &amp; Cabral &amp; Agra &amp; Lohmann" baseAuthorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Bignoniaceae" genus="Dolichandra" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Dolichandra hispida" order="Lamiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hispida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">Dolichandra hispida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vs. green in 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Bignoniaceae" genus="Dolichandra" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Dolichandra uncata" order="Lamiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="uncata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">Dolichandra uncata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and seed wing morphology (hyaline in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. H. Fonseca &amp; L. G. Lohmann" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="Fonseca &amp; Cabral &amp; Agra &amp; Lohmann" baseAuthorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Bignoniaceae" genus="Dolichandra" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Dolichandra hispida" order="Lamiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hispida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">Dolichandra hispida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vs. woody in 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Bignoniaceae" genus="Dolichandra" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Dolichandra uncata" order="Lamiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="uncata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">Dolichandra uncata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) are clear, making the separation of these two species necessary. In addition, the difference in fruit length is also striking, with fruits being much longer in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. H. Fonseca &amp; L. G. Lohmann" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="Fonseca &amp; Cabral &amp; Agra &amp; Lohmann" baseAuthorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Bignoniaceae" genus="Dolichandra" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Dolichandra hispida" order="Lamiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hispida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">Dolichandra hispida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(77-125.8 cm) than in 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Bignoniaceae" genus="Dolichandra" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Dolichandra uncata" order="Lamiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="uncata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">Dolichandra uncata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(9.2-38.5 cm). In fact, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. H. Fonseca &amp; L. G. Lohmann" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="Fonseca &amp; Cabral &amp; Agra &amp; Lohmann" baseAuthorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Bignoniaceae" genus="Dolichandra" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Dolichandra hispida" order="Lamiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hispida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">Dolichandra hispida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
presents one of the longest fruits of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Bignoniaceae" genus="Dolichandra" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Lamiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Bignoniaceae</taxonomicName>
, and possibly one of longest capsules within the Angiosperms (Table 
<tableCitation captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. Comparison of Dolichandra hispida and Dolichandra uncata; non-overlapping characters are shown in bold." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/984292AF4D5F46228A2BD563980DF08D" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" tableUuid="984292AF4D5F46228A2BD563980DF08D">1</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption ID-Table-UUID="984292AF4D5F46228A2BD563980DF08D" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/984292AF4D5F46228A2BD563980DF08D" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" start="Table 1" startId="T1">
