<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="39" type="phenology">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="39">Phenology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="39">This species was collected in flower in September, October, November, December and January and in fruit in September, November, December, January and February.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="39" type="conservation status">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="39">Conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="39">
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. H. Fonseca &amp; L. G. Lohmann" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="Fonseca &amp; Cabral &amp; Agra &amp; Lohmann" baseAuthorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Bignoniaceae" genus="Dolichandra" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Dolichandra hispida" order="Lamiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hispida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">Dolichandra hispida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is here considered as Least Concern [LC] according to IUCN criteria (
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN" journalOrPublisher="IUCN, Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" refId="B9" refString="IUCN, 2012. IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria: Version 3.1. IUCN, Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK" title="IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria: Version 3.1" year="2012">IUCN 2012</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee" journalOrPublisher="IUCN, Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" publicationUrl="http://www.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuidelines.pdf" refId="B10" refString="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee, 2014. Guidelines for using the IUCN red list categories and criteria. Version 11., http://www.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuidelines.pdf" title="Guidelines for using the IUCN red list categories and criteria. Version 11" url="http://www.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuidelines.pdf" year="2014">IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee 2014</bibRefCitation>
). The extent of occurrence estimated for the species is 2,209,625.833 km2 and the estimated area of occupancy is 875.000 km2 (cell width of 5 km). Therefore this classification was established based on the wide distribution of the taxon, since no population data is available.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
